            "answer_text": "It totally depends on your passing percentage criterion. If it's 30% then it will be 9 marks. If it's 40% it means you've to take at least 12 marks to pass that exam. And if 50% or more you better score 15 or more. Example : 30% of 30 = x 30/100 * 30 = x Each Zeroes (numerator) will be cancel out by 100 (denominator). 3*3=x 9=x X=9 (minimum marks when percentage is 30%) Hope you easily understand. All the best of the luck ;) Any suggestions : please do comments as its my first answer. ",
