            },
            "answer_text": "As per the general standards followed by most of the institutes, the passing marked are usually 35% or 40%. If you consider 35% then from 30 one should get 10.5 Marks. (35%*30 = 0.35*30) If you consider 40% then from 30 one should get 12 Marks. (40%*30 = 0.4*30) However if this is for some company then keep in mind some companies keep cutoff Marks as high as 60%-70%. Companies keep such high percentage and treat the exam as elimination round. Thanks! ",
